summary.name: CO2 Concentration Dataset
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains monthly CO2 concentration measurements and adjusted CO2 concentration values from 1958 to 2020.

properties.description: The date of the CO2 concentration measurement.
The measured CO2 concentration in parts per million (ppm).
The adjusted CO2 concentration in parts per million (ppm), accounting for seasonal variations.
The month of the year when the CO2 concentration measurement was taken.

goals.question: What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of Date vs CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show how CO2 concentration has changed over the years and if there is any noticeable trend.

goals.question: What is the distribution of adjusted CO2 concentration?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the frequency distribution of adjusted CO2 concentration values and help identify any outliers or patterns.

goals.question: What is the relationship between CO2 concentration and month?
goals.visualization: box plot of Month vs CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is any seasonal variation in CO2 concentration and if certain months have higher or lower CO2 concentrations.

goals.question: What is the correlation between CO2 and adjusted CO2 concentration?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of CO2 vs adjusted_CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the relationship between the two variables and if there is a strong positive correlation between them.

goals.question: What is the average CO2 concentration over the years?
goals.visualization: bar chart of Date vs CO2 (aggregated by year)
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the average CO2 concentration for each year and help identify any significant changes or trends over time.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
    yearly_data = data.groupby('Year')['CO2'].mean().reset_index()
    
    ax = sns.barplot(x='Year', y='CO2', data=yearly_data)
    ax.set_title('What is the average CO2 concentration over the years?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
